% Experiments with acme(4)
% RaphaÃ«l Proust,
  Simon Castellan
% 2014

Integrating Merlin with acme via the 9p interface.

# Roadmap:

- testing on more machines/setups
- improving libraries
	- 9p client library
	- acme library (with support for addresses and such)
- factorisation
- support of multi-line locations
- stateful Merlin interaction
	- keep track of what merlin has been told
	- sync state through $NAMESPACE/merlin
	- (make a 9p server enabled merlin, mount in $NAMESPACE?)
- integrate with Merlin source tree


# Suport:

Dependencies (including build dependencies):

- ocaml9p (copy source files or tweak mkfile)
- yojson
- batteries
- unix and str
- mk(1)

Works on:

```
$ echo 
$ uname -a
Linux XXX 3.12.9-2-ARCH #1 SMP PREEMPT Fri Jan 31 10:22:54 CET 2014 x86_64 GNU/Linux
$ ocaml -version
The OCaml toplevel, version 4.01.0
$ ocamlmerlin -version
The Merlin toolkit version 1.4.1, for Ocaml 4.01.0
$ pacman -Qi plan9port
Name           : plan9port
Version        : 20131024-3
Architecture   : x86_64
Optional Deps  : python2: for the codereview script [installed]
Build Date     : Mon 27 Jan 2014 08:33:40 PM GMT
